Description: This is a rare stock Strat with the Fishman acoustic bridge/whammy bar. They were made for about a year in 2006. The acoustic bridge can be blended with the humbucker and single coil pickups into one amp, or it can be separated with a Y cord. The bridge and preamp alone cost $408. This one is in pristine condition and bares the 60th Anniversary badge. It's finished in translucent Honey Blond, an uncommon color. The neck has zero fret wear and sports a beautiful Rosewood slab fretboard. The original deluxe gig bag and manuals are included as well as a Fender Strap, new set of strings and picks.In 2006 the Fender Custom Shop released the very limited (75) Pete Townsend model with the same bridge but costing many thousands more. Check it out:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tYOxim6dUSUDemo: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EYkI8MRBTHMHere is info and specs:The Fender Deluxe Power Stratocaster electric guitar gives you a piezo Fishman Power Bridge pickup to blend with a trio of Tex-Mex pickups for an extreme level of tonal flexibility. The two single-coils and bridge humbucker are controlled by a 5-way selector and no-load tone control while the Fishman piezo has a tone control and all pickups share a master volume.
